<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#ffffff"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000080"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">HERATIC</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I haven't opened EQ yet and I was just wonder'n when I load it on is, there anything special to do, any recomedations, thx</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Timlagor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Be aware that you will need to take a fairly long time to patch it when you first load up.<P>Play the tutorial.<P>Don't believe anything the books tell you about stats (-or anything else)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Facemaker</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Timlagor, regarding book.<P>Ain't that the truth!  Sheesh whoever wrote that manual...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vizion</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Definitely do the tutorial.  It may seem dumb, but it sure does make life easier on you and those you would pester to answer questions answered in the tutorial.<P>P.S.  All the things you kill for experience in the tutorial are added to your first character's experience.<P>P.P.S.  j/k  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Koolmoodi</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">for your first character try to make a class that is easy to play, like a warrior,ranger,paladin,rogue or monk...i know these are all melee classes but thats what makes them so easy to play, no spells to worry about,(pally,ranger,and sk spells arent too complex and arent of that much use to make it hard to play)my first character was a warrior, and ive loved it</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jelen of Brell</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">About the stats - very true, do NOT listen to the books.<P>About picking a melee class.. Obviously this person has not played a casting class.<P>My first character was a Mage, my second a Shaman.  I play 8 characters now, intermixed Meleer's, Casters, priests and hybrids.<P>First off, rogues are NOT easy.  Probably one of the hardest classes to solo, and to learn to play a rogue correctly - i.e. using your Evade skills, positioning for backstabs, Instilling Doubt etc.. is just as hard as playing any caster.  In fact, most casters have certain advantages in battle, and have a much EASIER time soloing things if played correctly.<P>Pick a class you ENJOY, not one thats's necessarily "easy" .. <P>Some key points.<P>Pure casters (Mages/Ench/Necros/Wiz) put all your bonus points in Intelligence (at least most)<P>Priests (Clerics, Druids, Shamans) put all points in Wisdom (at least most)<P>Melee classes are harder to assign stats, must use your judgement based on what your class needs most, and what stats your race already excels in.  I think STR and DEX are important factors nonetheless.<P>Bards and Enchanters should have high charisma for charming/mezzing.<P>STR - how hard you hit, how often you hit, how much you can carry.<BR>DEX - proc's are effected by this, combat is slightly affected, channeling skill increase is affected by this<BR>STA - resistance to stuns, holding your breath, long runs, how many times you can swing that big heavy axe.<BR>AGI - affects AC, I think it helps with dodge and parry<BR>WIS - Priest type stat, affects your mana supply <BR>INT - Pure caster type stat, affects your mana supply<BR>CHA - affects how much vendors buy/sell things to you, and success of mezmerizing, charm spells<P>NOTE: The highest of your WIS or INT is known to affect how well you perform your trade skills (successes vs. failures)<P>Treat people right!<P>Just my two cents.<P>Jelen Melenkurion<BR>Mystical Avengers<BR>Level 40 Shaman (among many others)<BR>Brell Serilis Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vizion</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">"NOTE: The highest of your WIS or INT is known to affect how well you perform your trade skills (successes vs. failures)"<P>This depends on the skill.  Recently strength was made a factor in blacksmithing.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</FONT>
